
📘 README 1 — Case 1 (Master DB Only + Nginx Frontend)
# 🚀 Case 1: Master DB Only + Nginx Frontend

## 📌 Overview
Simple architecture:
- Nginx serves frontend (HTML)
- Flask handles APIs
- MySQL Master handles all operations

---

## 🧱 Architecture


Browser → Nginx → index.html → Flask API → Master DB


---

# 🖥️ 1. EC2 Setup

```bash id="r1b"
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip nginx -y
📁 2. Project Setup
mkdir case1
cd case1

Create:

app.py
db.py
config.py
requirements.txt
📦 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
🗄️ 4. MySQL (RDS) Setup
mysql -h <MASTER-ENDPOINT> -u admin -p
CREATE DATABASE employees;

USE employees;

CREATE TABLE employees (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    role VARCHAR(100)
);
🚀 5. Run Backend
python3 app.py

Backend:

http://localhost:5000
🌐 6. Nginx Frontend Setup
📄 Path (IMPORTANT FIXED)
/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
Create HTML
sudo nano /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h1>Case 1 - Master DB Only</h1>

<button onclick="getData()">GET Employees</button>

<script>
function getData() {
    fetch("/api/employees")
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(data => console.log(data));
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
Nginx Config
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
        root /usr/share/nginx/html;
        index index.html;
    }

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000/;
    }
}
Restart nginx
sudo systemctl restart nginx
🌍 Access
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>
📊 Flow

Browser → Nginx → Flask → Master DB

✔ Case 1 Summary
Simple system
No replica
No cache